<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,407 --> 00:00:35,203
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:35,286 --> 00:00:39,707
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,335 --> 00:00:48,299
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,383 --> 00:00:51,594
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,554 --> 00:00:54,847
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,931 --> 00:00:57,642
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,725 --> 00:01:02,522
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,689 --> 00:01:07,902
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:07,986 --> 00:01:11,364
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,447 --> 00:01:17,287
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:28,881
LOVE

17
00:01:28,965 --> 00:01:32,927
YAGAMI

18
00:01:32,927 --> 00:01:33,428
<i>Light, Ryuzaki says he wants
you to help with the investigation.</i>

19
00:01:34,262 --> 00:01:36,180
<i>If you're interested,
come here immediately.</i>

20
00:01:37,140 --> 00:01:38,266
Okay, Dad.

21
00:01:40,518 --> 00:01:43,396
<i>Just as I was thinking about
how to get in...</i>

22
00:01:43,688 --> 00:01:45,773
<i>I never thought L himself
would ask me.</i>

23
00:01:46,858 --> 00:01:48,943
<i>Now I can get inside information
about the investigation...</i>

24
00:01:49,027 --> 00:01:51,654
<i>and about the fake Kira.</i>

25
00:01:52,614 --> 00:01:54,490
<i>Ineed to find out about Fake Kira</i>

26
00:01:54,574 --> 00:01:57,785
<i>before anyone else at
task force headquarters does...</i>

27
00:02:00,163 --> 00:02:01,539
Thank you, Yagami.

28
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,082
Not at all.

29
00:02:03,207 --> 00:02:05,710
Ryuga, we both want to catch Kira.

30
00:02:06,294 --> 00:02:08,546
Please call me Ryuzaki here.

31
00:02:09,464 --> 00:02:10,548
I'm Matsui.

32
00:02:10,632 --> 00:02:11,633
I'm Aihara.

33
00:02:11,841 --> 00:02:13,384
And I'm Asahi...

34
00:02:14,761 --> 00:02:15,845
I see.

35
00:02:16,262 --> 00:02:18,723
Well, would it be all right if
I'm Light Asahi?

36
00:02:19,223 --> 00:02:23,519
Please do. I will call you Light here.

37
00:02:24,604 --> 00:02:25,897
Now onto business.

38
00:02:26,397 --> 00:02:28,816
Please take a look at
our current information on Kira.

39
00:02:29,108 --> 00:02:31,110
I also want you to examine this video,
which was sent to the television station...

40
00:02:31,194 --> 00:02:33,696
but was never released to the public.

41
00:02:34,781 --> 00:02:38,451
Taking any material from this room
or taking notes is forbidden.

42
00:02:38,826 --> 00:02:39,827
I understand.

43
00:02:40,244 --> 00:02:41,412
We shall now begin.

44
00:02:44,874 --> 00:02:46,042
Light...

45
00:02:48,044 --> 00:02:49,754
THE PREVIOUS NIGHT

46
00:02:49,754 --> 00:02:52,590
We're going to hide the possibility
that there is a second Kira,

47
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:56,719
and ask Light Yagami
to investigate with us.

48
00:02:57,303 --> 00:03:00,264
B-But wouldn't that make it difficult
for Light to help with the investigation?

49
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:03,976
That's right. Why do you want him
to work with us anyway?

50
00:03:04,435 --> 00:03:06,312
We're only going
to hide that from him...

51
00:03:06,771 --> 00:03:10,608
until we have him watch this tape
and ask him for his impression of it.

52
00:03:11,192 --> 00:03:14,070
There's something amazing
about Light's reasoning skills.

53
00:03:14,529 --> 00:03:15,738
When he sees this,

54
00:03:15,988 --> 00:03:19,367
he may even deduce that
there is a second Kira.

55
00:03:20,243 --> 00:03:23,746
But the only basis for
a second Kira is your explanation

56
00:03:23,830 --> 00:03:26,374
that the victims of those killings
had committed minor crimes

57
00:03:26,457 --> 00:03:29,419
that never would have been
punished by Kira.

58
00:03:30,378 --> 00:03:31,629
That's not all.

59
00:03:32,296 --> 00:03:37,510
The Kira that we've presumed until now
needed a face and a name to kill.

60
00:03:38,678 --> 00:03:40,638
But judging from the fact that
Mr. Ukita was killed

61
00:03:40,722 --> 00:03:43,391
as soon as he arrived at
the television station,

62
00:03:44,308 --> 00:03:46,936
and considering how Kira practically
told me that he could kill me

63
00:03:47,019 --> 00:03:48,312
if "L" appeared on

64
00:03:49,522 --> 00:03:53,109
means that the Second Kira can kill
by just seeing someone's face.

65
00:03:54,986 --> 00:03:58,322
So, I'll ask Light to look
at the investigative facts and the video.

66
00:03:58,656 --> 00:04:01,659
If he suggests that there may
be a second Kira,

67
00:04:01,743 --> 00:04:04,495
then he's almost completely cleared.

68
00:04:04,829 --> 00:04:06,706
Ryuzaki, what do you mean?

69
00:04:07,623 --> 00:04:10,251
If he's Kira, he'll want to kill me,

70
00:04:10,334 --> 00:04:13,045
the one in charge of
the investigation.

71
00:04:14,005 --> 00:04:17,175
At this rate, if I go along with
the Second Kira's demands

72
00:04:17,467 --> 00:04:20,178
and appear three days later on TV,
I will die.

73
00:04:21,262 --> 00:04:25,349
I don't think that Kira would miss
an easy chance to kill me.

74
00:04:25,975 --> 00:04:26,851
So what you're saying is that

75
00:04:26,934 --> 00:04:29,437
if my son doesn't deduce that
there is a second Kira,

76
00:04:29,687 --> 00:04:31,522
then you'll continue to suspect him?

77
00:04:31,981 --> 00:04:35,568
No. In that case, it will remain below
a five-percent chance.

78
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:37,445
And we'll tell him that

79
00:04:37,570 --> 00:04:41,741
we are investigating the possibility of
a second Kira and have him assist us.

80
00:04:45,453 --> 00:04:50,208
<i>I trust you now believe
that I'm Kira.</i>

81
00:04:51,209 --> 00:04:53,711
<i>- Could it be that the reason...
- On the given day and time...</i>

82
00:04:53,795 --> 00:04:55,296
<i>why I feel so disgusted
when I watch this...</i>

83
00:04:55,379 --> 00:04:57,381
<i>is because I'm the real Kira?</i>

84
00:04:57,715 --> 00:05:00,718
<i>This is about more than just
tarnishing Kira's reputation.</i>

85
00:05:01,719 --> 00:05:02,804
<i>So why isn't...</i>

86
00:05:03,054 --> 00:05:05,807
<i>...anyone giving me any explanation
about this video?</i>

87
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:07,391
<i>That's strange...</i>

88
00:05:08,351 --> 00:05:09,727
<i>Well, whatever the case,</i>

89
00:05:09,811 --> 00:05:13,815
<i>I won't say anything careless
about this video.</i>

90
00:05:14,732 --> 00:05:16,651
<i>If I leave the situation alone,
I will die.</i>

91
00:05:18,069 --> 00:05:21,405
Light, what do you think?
Did you get something from it?

92
00:05:21,948 --> 00:05:22,949
Hmm?

93
00:05:24,951 --> 00:05:25,993
<i>Damn him!</i>

94
00:05:27,829 --> 00:05:31,207
There may be more than one person
who has Kira's power.

95
00:05:31,499 --> 00:05:34,752
Kira's power?!
Light, what do you mean?!

96
00:05:35,419 --> 00:05:36,712
There is a good chance that

97
00:05:36,838 --> 00:05:39,090
this is not the Kira
we've known up to now.

98
00:05:39,632 --> 00:05:43,970
Up to now, Kira's never used suspects
like these for his announced killings.

99
00:05:44,762 --> 00:05:48,641
And if Kira needs a face
and a name to kill...

100
00:05:49,058 --> 00:05:51,686
isn't it strange that he was able
to kill the detective and officers

101
00:05:51,769 --> 00:05:53,813
who happened to go to
the television studios?

102
00:05:54,230 --> 00:05:55,690
It's the same.

103
00:05:55,940 --> 00:05:59,694
It's exactly the same deduction as L,
I mean Ryuzaki.

104
00:06:00,027 --> 00:06:01,988
<i>You did well, Light.</i>

105
00:06:02,488 --> 00:06:04,824
<i>You should be cleared now...</i>

106
00:06:05,491 --> 00:06:07,243
That's right, Light.

107
00:06:07,952 --> 00:06:10,538
I also think we are looking
at a second Kira.

108
00:06:11,038 --> 00:06:12,123
<i>I thought so...</i>

109
00:06:12,874 --> 00:06:16,085
So you knew, Ryuga,
I mean Ryuzaki?

110
00:06:16,711 --> 00:06:18,796
Did you test me, knowing that?

111
00:06:19,255 --> 00:06:20,965
I didn't test you.

112
00:06:21,465 --> 00:06:25,678
It's not convincing if I'm the only one
who argues that there is a second Kira.

113
00:06:26,470 --> 00:06:28,598
With you coming to
the same conclusion as I did,

114
00:06:28,764 --> 00:06:30,641
my theory becomes more believable.

115
00:06:31,434 --> 00:06:34,937
You've been of great assistance to me,
Light. Thank you so much.

116
00:06:35,897 --> 00:06:37,148
So, it's decided.

117
00:06:37,857 --> 00:06:40,443
We first have to stop the second Kira.

118
00:06:40,985 --> 00:06:45,072
He obviously sympathizes with Kira,
and is not very bright.

119
00:06:46,032 --> 00:06:48,826
I think he'll obey the real Kira.

120
00:06:49,410 --> 00:06:52,413
So if we make a fake message
from the real Kira,

121
00:06:52,496 --> 00:06:54,123
there is a good chance that
we can stop him.

122
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:56,918
As I expected of you, Ryuzaki.

123
00:06:57,793 --> 00:07:00,087
I also thought that would
be the best idea.

124
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,214
Light...

125
00:07:02,965 --> 00:07:05,217
I would like you to play
the part of the real Kira.

126
00:07:06,344 --> 00:07:07,595
M-Me?

127
00:07:08,137 --> 00:07:11,849
Yes. With your abilities,
you should be able to do it.

128
00:07:12,433 --> 00:07:14,018
At any rate, we don't have
any time to waste.

129
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:16,354
Could you script a message
from Kira...

130
00:07:16,562 --> 00:07:19,690
to air on tonight's news?

131
00:07:21,692 --> 00:07:22,693
<i>Damn him...</i>

132
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:26,364
<i>He planned from the beginning
to bring me here to play this role.</i>

133
00:07:28,532 --> 00:07:30,368
Ryuzaki, is this all right?

134
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,870
I think I've portrayed
Kira convincingly.

135
00:07:35,122 --> 00:07:37,041
I think this is very good,

136
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:40,461
but if we don't remove the part
which says, "You're free to kill L,"

137
00:07:41,045 --> 00:07:42,213
I'll die.

138
00:07:44,465 --> 00:07:46,467
Well, when pretending to be Kira,

139
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:50,638
I thought that he would
demand that "L" be killed.

140
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:52,515
It's just a bit of a joke.

141
00:07:53,057 --> 00:07:55,059
You can change that to
whatever you like.

142
00:07:55,142 --> 00:07:56,185
Yes.

143
00:07:57,228 --> 00:08:00,398
Mr. Aihara, the script is ready.
I leave it to you.

144
00:08:00,856 --> 00:08:01,899
All right.

145
00:08:02,733 --> 00:08:04,151
<i>And now a shocking development.</i>

146
00:08:04,986 --> 00:08:08,948
<i>In response to the video that was sent
and aired on Sakura TV a few days ago,</i>

147
00:08:09,407 --> 00:08:12,702
<i>another person claiming to be
the real Kira has appeared.</i>

148
00:08:13,536 --> 00:08:18,791
<i>He has ordered several
television stations to air his message.</i>

149
00:08:19,417 --> 00:08:23,129
<i>The police department has
authorized us to broadcast this video.</i>

150
00:08:24,714 --> 00:08:27,425
<i>Is this the real Kira?
Is this another Kira?</i>

151
00:08:28,342 --> 00:08:31,429
<i>First, please take a look at the video.</i>

152
00:08:33,347 --> 00:08:34,432
<i>I am Kira.</i>

153
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:36,934
I did it! Kira responded!

154
00:08:37,935 --> 00:08:39,603
<i>I am the real Kira.</i>

155
00:08:39,937 --> 00:08:44,817
<i>The Kira who was on Sakura TV
a few days ago is not.</i>

156
00:08:46,110 --> 00:08:48,946
<i>I will show leniency
to the impostor</i>

157
00:08:49,155 --> 00:08:55,244
<i>because I am assuming he did it
out of an attempt to help me.</i>

158
00:08:55,745 --> 00:09:01,125
<i>But killing the innocent is
against my beliefs.</i>

159
00:09:01,625 --> 00:09:07,214
<i>If the impostor truly sympathizes
with me and wants to help my cause...</i>

160
00:09:07,923 --> 00:09:12,928
<i>I ask that he refrain from killing aimlessly
and accept my basic principles.</i>

161
00:09:13,637 --> 00:09:15,973
- /f you ignore fh/ls warning. - -
- All right! The video, the video!

162
00:09:16,766 --> 00:09:18,476
<i>- And continue f0 be reckless...
- What are you planning to do?</i>

163
00:09:18,559 --> 00:09:22,146
I'm going to reply to him,
of course.

164
00:09:23,064 --> 00:09:26,901
SEVERAL DAYS LATER

165
00:09:27,026 --> 00:09:28,819
- What?!
- It's here!

166
00:09:29,153 --> 00:09:31,989
<i>I will bring the entire
envelope there, but...</i>

167
00:09:32,323 --> 00:09:36,077
<i>for the time being, I'll play
a copy through the computer.</i>

168
00:09:39,038 --> 00:09:41,665
<i>Mr. Kira, thank you for your reply.</i>

169
00:09:42,291 --> 00:09:44,502
<i>I will do as you say.</i>

170
00:09:44,919 --> 00:09:46,504
- Wow!
- We did it!

171
00:09:46,879 --> 00:09:51,759
<i>"I will do as you say," huh?
I don't know if I can use him.</i>

172
00:09:52,384 --> 00:09:54,970
<i>If he really knows Kira's feelings,</i>

173
00:09:55,221 --> 00:09:58,182
<i>he would force L to appear
on TV and kill him.</i>

174
00:09:58,891 --> 00:10:01,185
<i>Don't fall for something like this...
Damn it!</i>

175
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:04,146
<i>I want to meet you.</i>

176
00:10:04,897 --> 00:10:06,982
<i>I don't think you have the eyes, but...</i>

177
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:10,111
<i>I won't try to kill you.</i>

178
00:10:10,361 --> 00:10:11,695
<i>Please don't worry.</i>

179
00:10:13,030 --> 00:10:14,198
<i>Is he stupid?</i>

180
00:10:14,698 --> 00:10:17,868
<i>He talked about the Shinigami eyes
on a tape the whole world will see?</i>

181
00:10:18,953 --> 00:10:20,621
He just said that he didn't
have "the eyes," didn't he?

182
00:10:20,996 --> 00:10:21,997
What could that mean?

183
00:10:22,081 --> 00:10:23,082
Who knows...?

184
00:10:23,749 --> 00:10:28,087
<i>Please think of a We y We can meet
Without the police knowing.</i>

185
00:10:29,004 --> 00:10:30,047
<i>When we meet,</i>

186
00:10:30,131 --> 00:10:32,883
<i>we can confirm each other,
by showing our Shinigami.</i>

187
00:10:33,843 --> 00:10:34,844
Shinigami?!

188
00:10:34,927 --> 00:10:35,928
<i>He's no good.</i>

189
00:10:36,428 --> 00:10:38,222
<i>I have to do something fast
about this guy, or else...</i>

190
00:10:39,265 --> 00:10:40,266
What?!

191
00:10:46,438 --> 00:10:47,731
Ryuzaki!

192
00:10:48,315 --> 00:10:49,275
Are you all right?!

193
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:50,651
Sh...

194
00:10:51,235 --> 00:10:52,403
Shinimgarni?!

195
00:10:53,946 --> 00:10:57,741
Are we supposed to accept
the existence of something like that?

196
00:11:09,837 --> 00:11:11,046
Shinigami?

197
00:11:12,298 --> 00:11:16,218
Are we supposed to accept
the existence of something like that?

198
00:11:17,219 --> 00:11:18,637
Impossible...

199
00:11:19,013 --> 00:11:20,556
There's no such thing...

200
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:25,186
That's right, Ryuzaki.
Shinigami don't exist.

201
00:11:28,105 --> 00:11:33,569
Kira had those criminals in prison
write something about Shinigami...

202
00:11:34,403 --> 00:11:38,490
So shouldn't we assume that
this is the same Kira?

203
00:11:39,074 --> 00:11:41,368
It's the same person,
so they say the same things.

204
00:11:41,702 --> 00:11:43,204
That can't be, Dad.

205
00:11:43,913 --> 00:11:49,251
If this is the same Kira from before,
he wouldn't have replied to our video.

206
00:11:50,419 --> 00:11:52,922
There is no way that the real Kira
would go through the trouble

207
00:11:53,005 --> 00:11:56,759
of getting L to appear on TV,
only to stop trying to kill him.

208
00:11:57,384 --> 00:11:59,678
Then maybe the real Kira and
the Second Kira...

209
00:11:59,762 --> 00:12:01,513
already have established
a connection.

210
00:12:01,597 --> 00:12:05,267
And decided to use the word "Shinigami"
to throw off the investigation.

211
00:12:05,476 --> 00:12:06,977
That's also not possible.

212
00:12:08,437 --> 00:12:09,855
<i>It's as</i> Light <i>says.</i>

213
00:12:09,939 --> 00:12:11,482
If the two Kiras were connected,

214
00:12:11,607 --> 00:12:14,735
I don't think that he would stop
trying to kill me.

215
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:20,658
Second Kira is acting
independent of the first.

216
00:12:21,742 --> 00:12:24,578
They want to meet the real Kira.

217
00:12:25,246 --> 00:12:28,624
That's right. They're acting
out of interest in Kira.

218
00:12:30,292 --> 00:12:33,879
"Shinigami" probably refers to
their killing power.

219
00:12:34,713 --> 00:12:37,591
"We can confirm our identities by showing
our Shinigami to each other,"

220
00:12:37,716 --> 00:12:38,926
probably means...

221
00:12:39,134 --> 00:12:42,680
"We can confirm our identities by
showing each other our killing power."

222
00:12:44,265 --> 00:12:45,432
That's right.

223
00:12:46,475 --> 00:12:48,811
The word "Shinigami" is
a word that has

224
00:12:49,311 --> 00:12:53,983
some meaning between
Kira and Second Kira.

225
00:12:55,276 --> 00:12:58,362
We should try to get him to
tell us what it means.

226
00:12:59,321 --> 00:13:01,657
So are you going to respond
and force him to be more direct?

227
00:13:02,366 --> 00:13:08,038
If we don't ask him properly,
he'll know that we're not Kira.

228
00:13:08,914 --> 00:13:12,918
No, I shall leave the rest to
Kira and Second Kira.

229
00:13:13,836 --> 00:13:14,878
Leave it to them?

230
00:13:15,462 --> 00:13:21,343
We can assume the second Kira is
satisfied after receiving a reply from Kira.

231
00:13:22,386 --> 00:13:25,597
He thinks that
he's got Kira's attention.

232
00:13:26,765 --> 00:13:29,727
And he also used a word that
only the two of them would understand.

233
00:13:31,186 --> 00:13:34,857
This reply will air today on
Sakura TV's six o'clock news.

234
00:13:35,482 --> 00:13:37,943
Of course, Kira should be watching
the exchange

235
00:13:38,027 --> 00:13:41,196
between our made-up Kira
and the Second Kira.

236
00:13:42,406 --> 00:13:45,326
From Kira's viewpoint, he'll want
to prevent the Second Kira from coming

237
00:13:45,409 --> 00:13:48,370
into direct contact with the police.

238
00:13:50,122 --> 00:13:54,835
Maybe this time,
the real Kira will respond.

239
00:13:56,712 --> 00:13:59,590
But what if Kira doesn't reply?

240
00:14:00,257 --> 00:14:04,553
Yes... I thought of what we could do
with the Second Kira in that case, but...

241
00:14:05,429 --> 00:14:09,350
If he reveals more information that
Kira doesn't want the police to know,

242
00:14:09,767 --> 00:14:11,852
and makes Kira more nervous
and furious,

243
00:14:11,935 --> 00:14:13,854
in order to pressure Kira
into meeting him...

244
00:14:14,396 --> 00:14:15,689
That would be interesting.

245
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:18,108
It would be more interesting...

246
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:21,487
if Kira gets scared and sends a reply
in order to avoid that.

247
00:14:22,196 --> 00:14:26,367
Then there's a chance we could obtain
some physical evidence from Kira himself.

248
00:14:27,576 --> 00:14:28,994
In the meantime,

249
00:14:29,078 --> 00:14:31,580
let's focus on gathering all the information
we can from the Second Kira's package.

250
00:14:36,085 --> 00:14:37,378
That's good...

251
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:39,963
Just like that!

252
00:14:42,257 --> 00:14:44,510
That was great, just great, Misa.

253
00:14:44,593 --> 00:14:45,677
That was wonderful!

254
00:14:47,513 --> 00:14:49,890
I'm worn out...

255
00:14:50,265 --> 00:14:53,018
Modeling sure uses a lot of energy!

256
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:55,813
Hey, Rem.

257
00:14:57,022 --> 00:14:58,440
Can I ask you something?

258
00:14:59,024 --> 00:14:59,983
What is it?

259
00:15:00,526 --> 00:15:03,445
Shinigami always have to have
a Death Note.

260
00:15:03,904 --> 00:15:05,823
Soto give one to a human
to play with,

261
00:15:05,906 --> 00:15:07,741
the Shinigami needs to have
two Death Notes...

262
00:15:08,242 --> 00:15:10,160
That means that Ryuk,
who gave the extra Death Note to Kira,

263
00:15:10,452 --> 00:15:14,164
was able to trick the Shinigami King
and get two, right?

264
00:15:14,873 --> 00:15:15,833
Right.

265
00:15:16,208 --> 00:15:17,251
Then you too?

266
00:15:17,626 --> 00:15:22,131
No. The Shinigami King
isn't fooled that easily.

267
00:15:22,673 --> 00:15:24,133
Then how?

268
00:15:25,134 --> 00:15:28,303
I'll just say... I'm one of the few
in the Shinigami Realm

269
00:15:28,429 --> 00:15:34,476
who know how to kill a Shinigami.

270
00:15:35,102 --> 00:15:40,566
Oh, then you killed a Shinigami
and gave his notebook to me.

271
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:44,153
No. I didn't kill him.

272
00:15:44,778 --> 00:15:49,074
I just happened to be around
when a Shinigami died...

273
00:15:49,992 --> 00:15:52,828
So, tell me how to kill a Shinigami.

274
00:15:54,663 --> 00:15:56,248
Don't tell anyone, okay?

275
00:15:57,708 --> 00:16:00,419
The way to kill a Shinigami...

276
00:16:01,837 --> 00:16:04,381
is to make them fall
in love with a human.

277
00:16:08,051 --> 00:16:09,803
What a beautiful way to kill.

278
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:20,439
There once was a Shinigami
named Gelus

279
00:16:20,522 --> 00:16:24,401
who used to watch a girl
from the Shinigami Realm.

280
00:16:25,110 --> 00:16:29,990
Gelus was always looking
at that girl from the Shinigami Realm.

281
00:16:40,834 --> 00:16:43,212
It's today, isn't it?
The end of her life.

282
00:16:44,630 --> 00:16:47,883
She looks so healthy.
Why today?

283
00:16:50,052 --> 00:16:51,053
Why...

284
00:16:52,012 --> 00:16:53,055
today?

285
00:16:58,644 --> 00:17:01,438
I wanted to know how
she was going to die too,

286
00:17:01,522 --> 00:17:03,857
and decided to watch with him.

287
00:17:08,070 --> 00:17:10,906
The girl was walking alone
at night on the street.

288
00:17:12,741 --> 00:17:13,784
And then...

289
00:17:18,455 --> 00:17:19,748
Suddenly from an alley,

290
00:17:19,831 --> 00:17:23,627
a man appeared and confessed
his love for the girl.

291
00:17:24,253 --> 00:17:25,879
I love you more
than anyone else in the world!

292
00:17:26,004 --> 00:17:28,006
I'm always watching you!
I want to protect you forever!

293
00:17:28,882 --> 00:17:30,759
It was a man she didn't know.

294
00:17:30,968 --> 00:17:33,011
The girl turned him down, of course.

295
00:17:39,268 --> 00:17:42,521
Then...I'll kill you...

296
00:17:43,063 --> 00:17:44,773
Then kill myself-!

297
00:17:50,237 --> 00:17:51,280
H-Hey.

298
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:52,573
Stop!

299
00:17:55,617 --> 00:17:59,705
Gelus did something that
a Shinigami should never do.

300
00:18:15,178 --> 00:18:19,808
Gelus used his Death Note
to save the girl.

301
00:18:21,476 --> 00:18:22,811
But that was not good.

302
00:18:25,063 --> 00:18:31,653
Shinigami shorten human lives.
They only exist to take lives.

303
00:18:48,128 --> 00:18:49,671
At that moment,

304
00:18:49,755 --> 00:18:54,843
Gelus became something which was
neither sand nor rust, and died.

305
00:18:57,346 --> 00:19:00,432
Only his Death Note was left.

306
00:19:04,353 --> 00:19:11,401
Then Gelus' remaining life span was
transferred to the girl whose life he saved.

307
00:19:14,863 --> 00:19:16,740
Does that mean that the Shinigami
wouldn't have died

308
00:19:17,032 --> 00:19:19,368
if he hadn't fallen in love
with that girl?

309
00:19:19,993 --> 00:19:21,036
That's right.

310
00:19:24,414 --> 00:19:25,749
So...

311
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:31,505
It was a Shinigami named Gelus
who saved me that day.

312
00:19:32,339 --> 00:19:33,382
Yes.

313
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:36,259
Gelus was in love with you.

314
00:19:37,969 --> 00:19:40,555
So that notebook is yours.

315
00:19:42,432 --> 00:19:43,475
Yeah...

316
00:19:46,853 --> 00:19:49,648
I see. In order to kill a Shinigami

317
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:52,943
you need him to fall in love with
a human and save that person.

318
00:19:53,485 --> 00:19:57,030
What about you, Rem?
Are you in love with me?

319
00:19:57,531 --> 00:20:01,326
Give it up. You can't kill me.

320
00:20:02,119 --> 00:20:03,704
Oh? You figured it out?

321
00:20:05,831 --> 00:20:09,710
But now I have something
I can tell Kira.

322
00:20:10,377 --> 00:20:15,340
I wonder if he knows?
How to kill a Shinigami?

323
00:20:17,092 --> 00:20:21,513
I asked him on TV,
"Please tell me how I can meet you,"

324
00:20:21,596 --> 00:20:23,598
but he hasn't replied.

325
00:20:24,599 --> 00:20:27,060
Maybe I should send him
another message.

326
00:20:30,439 --> 00:20:31,523
<i>This isn't good...</i>

327
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:35,026
<i>I can't leave the Second Kira
alone like this.</i>

328
00:20:35,944 --> 00:20:38,780
<i>If the Second Kira makes
a fatal slip-up</i>

329
00:20:38,864 --> 00:20:40,574
<i>and is caught by the police,</i>

330
00:20:40,949 --> 00:20:43,618
<i>there 11s a chance that the police
will find out about the Death Note.</i>

331
00:20:46,288 --> 00:20:47,289
Welcome.

332
00:20:48,915 --> 00:20:50,375
A strawberry sundae, please.

333
00:20:51,209 --> 00:20:52,252
Certainly.

334
00:20:53,962 --> 00:20:55,338
<i>So what should I do?</i>

335
00:20:55,797 --> 00:20:59,092
<i>How can I contact the Second Kira
without L noticing?</i>

336
00:21:00,719 --> 00:21:01,803
Thank you for waiting.

337
00:21:05,474 --> 00:21:08,810
<i>I want to meet Kira soon!</i>

338
00:21:09,603 --> 00:21:10,687
<i>But at any rate...</i>

339
00:21:11,104 --> 00:21:13,899
<i>What kind of a person are you,
Fake lfira ?</i>

340
00:21:14,858 --> 00:21:17,778
<i>What kind of a person are you, Kira?</i>

341
00:21:23,116 --> 00:21:26,119
TO BE CONTINUED

342
00:21:26,453 --> 00:21:31,416
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

343
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:36,797
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

344
00:21:37,130 --> 00:21:40,342
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

345
00:21:40,425 --> 00:21:45,806
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

346
00:21:45,972 --> 00:21:52,229
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

347
00:21:52,312 --> 00:21:56,817
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

348
00:21:57,609 --> 00:22:02,489
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

349
00:22:02,697 --> 00:22:06,284
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

350
00:22:06,368 --> 00:22:09,955
<i>To accomplish</i>

351
00:22:10,539 --> 00:22:15,168
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

352
00:22:15,418 --> 00:22:20,799
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

353
00:22:20,882 --> 00:22:25,887
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

354
00:22:26,513 --> 00:22:31,726
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

355
00:22:36,064 --> 00:22:37,649
PREVIEW

356
00:22:37,649 --> 00:22:40,151
May 22nd, my friend and I showed
each other our notebooks in Aoyama.

357
00:22:40,318 --> 00:22:44,948
If Fake Kira is caught, I'll have to
get my hands on his notebook.

358
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:48,535
In the worst case scenario,
I may have to kill everyone there.

359
00:22:48,535 --> 00:22:51,079
NEXT EPISODE: CONFESSION

